Mar 19 2005	Not Bad	We spent 2 nights here in mid- March. Not as bad as the reviews had me expecting. The rooms are basic but fairly clean. Motel staff were very helpful; quickly providing additional pillows and a missing chair from my room(??) . Very good coffee in the motel lobby in the morning.  I would likely find a hotel more on the outskirts of the city next time.....and then use public transportation rather than renting a car. Parking is just impossible in San Francisco! Weekly or daily passes for the public systems are very affordable.	
Feb 24 2005	Great Value	I'm writing this review from the Best Inn Hotelon the corner of Chestnut &amp; Van Ness here in San Francisco. After reading the reviews from websites I was skeptical about coming here. On average, this hotel had only been rated at about a 60% recommendation rate. It's obviously not the Hilton or the Fairmont, but if you are looking for a place to stay for a great price, this place is for you. Our room (on the 2nd level) is completely renovated, has Free High-Speed Internet, a new 27&quot; TV, new furniture, and is extremely clean. The rooms are all equipped with an ironing board and hair dryer, soaps and shampoos, we got a free breakfast, and FREE parking with in and out privileges. The parking lot is really crammed, so there is double parking. Just to be safe, you want to make sure that you check in early in the daytime (before 4pm) to ensure you get a parking spot. The staff was friendly, and they gladly accepted the coupon (that we got in a Travel booklet from Denny’s) that have us the room for $49- No hesitations. We walked to Fisherman’s Wharf in 10 minutes, and we were at Pier 39 in 15 mins, can’t ask for a better location. My only caution is to those who are light sleepers. There is a lot of traffic on the street, and since the hotel is shaped like a U, the noise gets trapped in easily. I requested a wake up call, turned the clock radio on an easy listening radio station and slept like a log. It looks rough from the outside, but it’s worth a shot. In fact, the staff encouraged us to look at the room before we booked it. I will return to this hotel for sure.	
